	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Paste markdown templates (including images) into note.com editor.

Setup:
1. Choose a Python backend (NOTE_PYTHON_BACKEND workflow variable):
   - "uv" (default): install uv from https://astral.sh/uv — no global pip install needed
   - "global": run `pip3 install pyobjc-framework-Cocoa` in your system Python
2. Set NOTE_TEMPLATES_DIR to your templates folder (default: ~/Documents/Note Templates)
3. Create .md files using standard markdown image syntax: ![caption](./images/photo.png)
4. Open note.com editor in your browser
5. Trigger Alfred with keyword "note", select a template, press Enter</string>
